和我一起拨开迷雾，追寻真相，守望时代。
Join me as we move through the fog, seek the truth and keep watch.
。
.
长远来看，旅游行业仍是朝阳产业2月28日，曾获阿里投资、被称为“中国出境旅游O2O第一股”的百程旅行网启动清算准备。
In the long run, the tourism industry is still sunrise industry February 28, Ali investment, known as "O2O China Outbound Travel Unit 1" 100-way travel network to start the liquidation.
这家依靠签证业务导流的百程旅行在过去几年持续经营困难，意料之外的疫情成为压垮资金链的最后一根稻草。
The 100-way trip, which relies on the visa business, has run into trouble for the past few years, with an unexpected outbreak as the last straw in the financial chain.
实质上，受疫情冲击影响，整个旅游业损失惨重。
In essence, the impact of the epidemic has taken a heavy toll on the entire tourism industry.
北京第二外国语学院旅游管理学院院长厉新建表示，2020年春节期间中国整个旅游业的直接损失预计在5500亿元左右。
Li Xin, dean of the School of Tourism Management at the Beijing Second Foreign Studies Institute, said the direct cost to China's tourism industry during the 2020 Spring Festival was estimated at around 550 billion yuan.
世界旅游城市联合会首席专家魏小安认为，2019年中国旅游业总收入6.5万亿元，按此估算，平均停滞一天，旅游业即损失178亿元。
Wei Xiaoan, chief expert of the World Tourism Organization, reckons that with a total tourism revenue of 6.5 trillion yuan in 2019, tourism will lose 17.8 billion yuan after stagnating on average for one day.
百程曾在2016年4月挂牌新三板，成为O2O出境旅游第一股。
In April 2016, PepsiCo was listed in the new three boards, O2O Outbound Travel Unit 1.
作为有着风向标意义的企业、作为第一家在疫情后宣布关闭的旅游公司，百程旅行网会成为被推倒的第一张“多米诺骨牌”吗？冰冻之下，旅游业的出路到底在何方？破产的签证巨头公开资料显示，百程旅游网成立于2000年，以旅游签证业务起家，后拓展旅游目的地业务，于2008年3月获得富达亚洲、银瑞达千万美元A轮投资，于2014年3月完成由阿里牵头的近2000万美元B轮融资。
As a weathervane company, the first travel company to declare its closure after the outbreak, will EMN become the first domino to be pulled down.Under the ice, the bankrupt visa giant revealed that EMTN was founded in 2000 to start with a tourist visa business and expand its tourist destination business.
2016年6月登陆新三板后持续亏损，已于2019年7月摘牌。
The deficit continued after landing on the new board in June 2016 and was removed in July 2019.
百程旅行网2018年中期亏损额达到1285.64万元，亏损同比减少552.73万元。
In 2018, the company posted a mid-year loss of $12,856,400, a year-on-year decline of $5,527,300.
公司财报显示，亏损主要由于公司仍处于互联网行业公司业务拓展期，技术研发投入处于相对较高水平，同时市场竞争及人力成本变动因素对业务利润形成挤占。
The company reported that the loss is mainly due to the company is still in the Internet industry business expansion period, technology research and development investment in a relatively high level, while market competition and labor cost changes factors of business profits crowding out.
今年2月28日，百程旅行网发布的内部文件显示，公司决定启动清算准备，因受新冠疫情影响，资金不能维持公司继续运转。
On February 28th, internal documents released by the company showed that the company had decided to start liquidation preparations and could not sustain the company because of the new crown outbreak.
公司称将进行全面善后处理，并让员工提前做好自谋出路的准备。
The company said it would carry out comprehensive post-treatment and prepare employees for self-employment in advance.
在业内人士看来，疫情只是压倒百程的最后一根稻草。
For industry insiders, the epidemic is only the last straw to overwhelm the company.
过去，大众出入境政策的严苛与申请的繁杂，传统签证服务商可以利用信息差等方式获得不错的利润。
In the past, the rigours of mass entry and exit policies and the complexity of applications have allowed traditional visa service providers to make good profits by, for example, exploiting information gaps.
随着越来越多人熟悉了签证流程，尤其是不少使领馆减免了申请材料，放宽了申请条件，无疑压缩了这种以签证为切口和获客手段的生存空间。
As more and more people become familiar with the visa process, in particular a number of embassies and consulates reduced the application materials and relaxed the application conditions, there is no doubt that this visa-cut and access to the means of survival space.
艾媒咨询创始人兼CEO张毅向中国新闻周刊表示，百程旅行网的危机不能单单归结于疫情，身处高速增长的旅游业，却一直处于亏损状态，这表明还是企业在经营管理、商业模式上出现了问题。
Zhang Yi, founder and CEO of Media Consulting, told China News Weekly that the crisis could not be attributed solely to the epidemic, with a fast-growing tourism industry that has been running at a loss, suggesting problems with its business management and business model.
“企业消亡是很正常的事。
"It's quite normal for businesses to die.
”北京德和衡律师事务所主任刘克江向中国新闻周刊表示，不管是解散还是破产，都需依法成立清算组，清理公司财产和债权债务，办理通知、公告债权人，处理公司清偿债务后的剩余财产等事项。
Liu Kejiang, director of Beijing-based De Heng Law Firm, told China News Weekly that in case of dissolution or bankruptcy, a liquidation group should be set up according to law to liquidate the company's property and liabilities, handle notifications, announce creditors and dispose of the company's surplus property after paying off its debts.
从定义上来讲，企业清算是指企业按章程规定解散以及由于破产或其他原因宣布终止经营后，对企业的财产、债权、债务进行全面清查，并进行收取债权，清偿债务和分配剩余财产的经济活动。
By definition, liquidation of an enterprise means that, after dissolution in accordance with the provisions of its articles of association and the declaration of termination of its business due to bankruptcy or other reasons, a comprehensive inventory is made of the property, creditors' rights and liabilities of the enterprise, and economic activities are conducted to collect creditor's rights, repay debts and distribute surplus property.
对于百程旅行网的破产清算，品橙旅游创始人兼CEO王琢向中国新闻周刊表示，这是思路特别清晰、懂公司运营的理性人的一次处理方式。
'This is a way of dealing with rational people with very clear ideas and understanding of how the company operates, 'said Wang Zao, founder and CEO of Zheng Zhiwei Travel, a travel company for 100-way travel.
通过本次疫情能充分认识到，清算与注册一样，是理性、法制、负责任的商业选择。
Through this epidemic we can fully understand that liquidation, like registration, is a rational, legal and responsible business choice.
那么，作为有着风向标意义的旅游企业、作为第一家在疫情后宣布关闭的旅游公司，百程旅行网会成为被推倒的第一张“多米诺骨牌”吗？业内人士告诉中国新闻周刊，由于旅游业不属于重资产行业，其破产不会引起大的连锁反应，但在一定程度上会加快行业的整合速度，相比一些不清算不破产也不运营的僵尸企业，依法清算有序退场不失为一种负责任的举措。
So, as a weathervane tour operator, the first travel company to declare a shutdown after the outbreak, would BLN be the first domino to be pulled down? Industry insiders told China News Weekly that since tourism was not a heavy asset industry, its failure would not cause a major chain reaction, but would accelerate the industry's consolidation somewhat.
“肯定会有一批中小平台面临经营危机，这是正常的优胜劣汰。
"There will definitely be a bunch of small and medium-sized platforms facing an operational crisis.
”张毅表示，疫情结束后旅游业会迎来爆发性增长，对企业来说会是一个很好的机会。
Zhang said the explosive growth in tourism after the epidemic was over would be a good opportunity for companies.
停摆的旅游业百程旅行网破产清算的背后，是新冠肺炎疫情发生以来逐渐陷入停摆的旅游业。
Behind the collapse of the stalled tourism 100-way travel network is the tourism industry, which has been bogged down since the outbreak of pneumonia in New Crown.
1月24日，文化和旅游部发布紧急通知，要求全国旅行社及在线旅游企业暂停经营团队旅游及“机票+酒店”旅游产品，本来期盼能在春节前后迎来增长高峰的旅行社、景点、航空公司、酒店等相关企业瞬间陷入停摆，一场消费者集中退款潮迎面扑来，让各大旅游企业措手不及。
On January 24, the Ministry of Culture and Tourism issued an emergency notice calling on travel agencies and online tour operators nationwide to suspend group travel and "air ticket + hotel" travel products in the hope of bringing down travel agencies, attractions, airlines and hotels, which were expected to reach their peak growth rates around the Spring Festival holiday.
1月27日起，出境游也被陆续叫停。
Outbound travel has also been suspended since 27 January.
携程、飞猪、去哪儿等在线旅游平台公司也面临前所未有的“退票退款”危机，纷纷表示为了疫情退票已垫付票款超过10亿元。
Ctrip, Pig, where to go and other online travel platform companies are also facing an unprecedented "refund" crisis, said the outbreak of the refund has been more than 1 billion yuan in advance.
疫情对旅游业的冲击也由亚太地区向全球蔓延。
The impact of the epidemic on tourism has also spread from the Asia-Pacific region to the world.
日本爱知县老字号旅馆“富士见庄”于2月中旬宣布破产，德国汉堡中国之旅有限公司于2月21日向汉堡法院提起破产保护申请，日本神户夜光邮轮公司于3月2日宣布递交破产申请，被称为“酒店业拼多多”的印度独角兽OYO近日宣布将在全球范围内裁员约5000人……美国旅游协会3月3日预测，未来三个月到访美国的国际游客数量将下降6%，为2008年金融危机以来最大的国际入境游降幅。
Japan's Nighttime Hotels in Aichi Prefecture declared bankruptcy in mid-February, Germany's Hamburg China Cruises Ltd. filed for bankruptcy protection on February 21, and Japan's Kobe Night Guang Cruises announced on March 2 that it would lay off about 5,000 people worldwide.
全球在线旅游巨头Booking Holdings在一季度业绩指引中预测，房间预订量将下降5%-10%，旅行预订总量下降10%-15%，收入下降3%-7%。
Booking Holdings, the global online travel giant, predicts in its first-quarter earnings guidelines that room reservations will fall by 5% to 10%, total travel bookings by 10% to 15%, and revenue by 3% to 7%.
目前大中华区受到的波及最甚，亚太地区也受到不利影响，在新冠病毒出现在意大利之后几天，欧洲的预订量也出现下降。
Greater China has been hardest hit, and the Asia-Pacific region has been adversely affected, with bookings falling in Europe in the days after the emergence of the new crown virus in Italy.
冰冻之下，旅游业的出路到底在何方？携程董事局主席梁建章对媒体表示，短期来看国际业务还是各种取消、修改，所以短期会更着重做国内游。
Liang Jianzhang, chairman of Ctrip's board of directors, told the media that in the short term, the international business is still cancelled and modified, so more emphasis will be placed on domestic travel in the short term.
“出境游市场仍相对悲观，这部分需求会逐渐转化成以国内游为主、由近及远的一个过程。
"The outbound travel market is still relatively pessimistic, and this part of the demand will gradually become a domestic tourism-based process, from near to far.
” 北京第二外国语学院旅游科学学院副院长邓宁向中国新闻周刊表示，“周边游”有望最先开始回暖，人们往往不是去大城市、传统热门旅游目的地去聚集，而会首选气候适宜、疫情期间情况较好的目的地。
Deng Ning, vice-dean of the School of Tourism Sciences at the Beijing Second Foreign Studies Institute, told China News Weekly that "peripheral travel" is expected to begin first, with people often choosing destinations with better climates and better times than big cities and traditional tourist destinations.
相比传统意义上的跟团游，更多人会选择小团、散拼。
Compared with the traditional sense of tour, more people will choose small groups, scattered.
山西证券认为，受疫情扩散期间各部门政策收紧以及消费者旅游信心受损影响，出境游市场恢复仍需时间。
Shanxi Securities said it would take time for the outbound travel market to recover from the spread of the epidemic as a result of tighter policies in various sectors and impaired consumer tourism confidence.
而长远来看，旅游行业仍是朝阳产业，不会因黑天鹅危机阻挡行业发展。
In the long run, however, the tourism industry is still a sunrise industry and will not be held back by the Black Swan crisis.
为了帮扶行业渡过寒冬，一系列保障和激励政策也陆续出台。
In order to help the industry through the winter, a series of security and incentive policies have also been introduced.
2月5日，文旅部决定向旅行社暂退缴纳额80%的旅游服务质量保证金，暂退范围是全国已依法缴纳保证金、领取旅行社业务经营许可证的旅行社。
On 5 February, the Ministry of Tourism decided to suspend payment of 80 per cent of the travel service quality guarantee to the travel agency, which is a travel agency that has paid the deposit and received the travel agency's operating license according to law.
2月26日，文旅部市场管理司司长刘克智表示，截至2月25日，全国3.9万家旅行社共有3.52万家提出暂退质保金，应退保证金总额为80亿元，目前已退还34.62亿元。
On February 26, Liu Kezhi, director of the marketing management department of the Ministry of Culture and Tourism, said 35,200 travel agencies across the country had put forward 35,200 applications for surrender guarantees, with a total refundable deposit of 8 billion yuan, of which 3.462 billion yuan had been returned.
在地方层面，上海市文旅局于3月14日下发《关于本市旅游企业恢复部分经营活动的通知》，向全市旅行社传达了复工复产的好消息，除不得经营跨省（区、市）和出入境的团队旅游业务及“机票+酒店”旅游业务外，其他经营活动可正常展开。
At the local level, the Shanghai Bureau of Culture and Tourism issued the Notice on the Resumption of Part of the Business Activities of Tourism Enterprises in this Municipality on March 14, conveying the good news to the city's travel agencies on the resumption of operation.
此外，财政部、税务总局提出了旅游等四大类困难行业2020年度发生的亏损，最长结转年限由5年延长至8年，中国旅游协会对212家会员单位免除2020年会费。
In addition, the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation have raised losses in 2020 in four difficult sectors, such as tourism. The maximum carry-over period has been extended from five to eight years, and the China Tourism Association has exempted 212 members from the 2020 membership fee.
近日，中国旅游研究院院长戴斌在“逆风飞扬 绝地反弹”文旅振兴公益在线巅峰大会上表示，2020年的旅游战疫已由“停组团、关景区、防疫情”“托底线、救企业”，转入了“严格防控、有序复工”的新阶段。
Dai Bin, director of the China Tourism Research Institute, told a conference on revitalizing pro bono online peak of the Jedi Rebate against the Wind that the 2020 epidemic of tourism had been turned into a new stage of "strict prevention and orderly resumption of work" by "stopping tours, scenic spots, epidemic prevention," "bottom line support and enterprise rescue."
厉新建向中国新闻周刊表示，脆弱的行业需要韧性的增长，韧性增长不只是“打不死的小强”，而应成为一种持续机制；不能“好了伤疤忘了疼”，而应吃一堑长一智，不断修好护城河；不应见招拆招地应对不确定性的环境，而应未雨绸缪地增加确定性的能力。
"Fragile industries need resilient growth," Li told China News Weekly. "Resilient growth is not just an incurable little power," but a continuous mechanism. Instead of "healing scars and forgetting pain," it should be a continuous process of repairing moats.
“旅游业经历此次风雨过后，如果仍只顾看脚下的路，或许只能看到泥泞不堪，如果不忘抬头看天，或将看到绚烂美丽的彩虹。
"If the tourism industry, after this storm, is still only looking at the road under foot, may only see the quagmire, if do not forget to look up at the sky, or will see gorgeous rainbow.
”值班编辑：石若萧推荐阅读▼国际公共卫生专家：美国疫情防控迎来转折点，未来几周病例会迅速上升你知道现在最火本科专业是什么吗？学还是不学，这是个问题揍他可以。
